//Tendons - Pes anserinus

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 - Soft parts of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Tendons - Pes anserinus' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Layer' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tear' checkbox is enabled
And 'Enthesiopathy' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Layer' checkbox
Then 'Pars superficialis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pars profundus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tear' checkbox
Then 'Intramuscular' radio button is enabled
And 'Intratendinous' radio button is enabled
And 'Insertion' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hematoma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone bruise' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Retraction' radio button
Then 'Dimension in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'Enthesiopathy' checkbox
Then 'Thickening/Edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bursitis pes anserinus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Muscular atrophy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Articular effusion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Muscular atrophy' checkbox
Then 'Semitendinosus muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Gracilis muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sartorius muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Semimembranosus muscle (pes anserinus profundus)' checkbox is enabled